events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis and the Lakers might be starting to find their rhythm — just as the uncertainty of the NBA trade deadline approaches.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis has 3rd career triple-double, Lakers beat Hornets 124-118

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell was stuck in the foul lane after picking up his dribble, so he tossed the ball off the backboard to himself and dunked.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 29 as rolling Cavs improve to 14-1 in last 15 with 136-110 win over Kings

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving returned from a six-game absence because of a sprained thumb and led Dallas to a needed win. It also served as a warmup for what was ahead — a return to Brooklyn, where injuries and controversies led to a tumultuous tenure with the Nets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving, Doncic power Mavericks past 76ers without injured Embiid, 118-102

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 36 points, including 11 in the fourth quarter, and the Los Angeles Clippers finished off a long road trip in style with a 149-144 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard scores 36 to help Clippers top Hawks 149-144, finish road trip 6-1

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry looked at a box score that showed no Warriors but him made a 3-pointer.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 29 points, Warriors overcome slow start to beat the Nets 109-98

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — After Brandon Ingram hit five straight 3-pointers during the final three minutes of the third quarter, he had a big smile as he made his way to the bench and soaked in a prolonged standing ovation.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram hits 8 3s, scores 41 to lead Pelicans past struggling Raptors 138-100
